just bought one :) Not the gamer kit. The actual micro:bit board. It's such a cool little thing. I was talking to the woman who invented it. She said that kids have been making amazing things with it. Then she got a Ray Gun (for reals) out of her bag that some kids had been making. It was a plastic alien looking gun with a micro:bit attached to the top, a speaker on the back and a CO2 detector on the front. It was measuring CO2 in the air when you pulled the trigger. If the readings were too high the lights would flash "warning" and the buzzer would start going off. Really fucking smart. And that they distributed a million of them. Every 7 year old who requested one was allowed one wether they're in school, homeschool, not in education. Honestly, such a cool thing to be doing. Another kid was turning hers into a sensor that knew when it was falling so it could open a parachute. Nuts.
